userDoc.notice: Library for formatting _the request part_ of _the base messages_. - Request represents a message sender requirements for the message execution on the destination chain. - Request occupies a single storage word, and thus is stored on stack instead of being stored in memory. > gasDrop field is included for future compatibility and is ignored at the moment. # Request stack layout (from highest bits to lowest) | Position   | Field    | Type   | Bytes | Description                                          | | ---------- | -------- | ------ | ----- | ---------------------------------------------------- | | (024..012] | gasDrop  | uint96 | 12    | Minimum amount of gas token to drop to the recipient | | (012..004] | gasLimit | uint64 | 8     | Minimum amount of gas units to supply for execution  | | (004..000] | version  | uint32 | 4     | Base message version to pass to the recipient        |

SHIFT_GAS_DROP.details: Amount of bits to shift to gasDrop field

SHIFT_GAS_LIMIT.details: Amount of bits to shift to gasLimit field
